    <div class="content">
	
	
	<h2><img height="189" align="left" width="200" class="thumbnailimg" src="http://graphics.ics.uci.edu/drupal/img/charcoalindex.jpg" alt="Sample Image" /></h2>
<h2><strong>Non-Photo Realistic Rendering</strong></h2>
<p align="justify"><span class="left"><b>Overview:</b> We present simple rendering techniques implemented using traditional graphics hardware to achieve the effects of charcoal drawing. The effects include characteristics of charcoal drawings like broad grainy strokes and smooth tonal variations that are achieved by smudging the charcoal by hand. Further, we also generate the closure effect that is used by artists at times to avoid hard silhouette edges. All these effects are achieved using contrast enhancement operators on textures and/or colors of the 3D model.</span></p>
<p>Publications:</p>
<table bordercolor="#FFFFFF" border="1" width="100%">
    
        <tr>
            <td><img height="120" width="240" class="thumbnailimg" alt="" src="http://graphics.ics.uci.edu/drupal/img/2002d.jpg" /></td>
            <td><strong>Hardware Accelerated Real Time Charcoal Rendering</strong><br />
            <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~majumder/">Aditi Majumder</a>, <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~gopi/">M. Gopi</a> <br />
            <em>Symposium of Non-Photorealistic Amination and Rendering, 2002</em><br />
            <a href="http://graphics.ics.uci.edu/upload/NPAR02.pdf">paper</a> <a href="http://graphics.ics.uci.edu/upload/egrw01.mpg">video</a></td>
        </tr>
    
</table>
<p>Project Members: M. Gopi, Aditi Majumder</p>
